  fishName: Flying fish
  latinName: Exocoetus volitans
  habitat: ' tropical and subtropical zones of all the world''s oceans. Its range
    includes the Caribbean Sea and the western part of the Mediterranean Sea'
  description: To help them hide from predators looking up from the deep ocean, their
    backs are shiny blue, and their bellies are bright silverTheir tails have an
    uneven shape, with the bottom part being much longer than the top. They use this
    tail to kick the water and get extra speed just before taking off. Do you know
    that Flying fish are amazing ocean creatures known for their ability to jump
    out of the water and glide through the air. While they can't flap their wings
    like birds, they can soar above the waves for hundreds of feet to escape hungry
    predators like tuna and swordfish.
  conservationStatus: least concern
